  • Easy Setup：With Matter, Skip the step of downloading and registering multiple manufacturers' apps every time you buy a new device. Instead, head straight to certified smart home platforms like Apple Home, Alexa, Google Home, SmartThings, to control all your Matter devices.【TIP】Matter-certified hub or controller (HomePod, Echo Dot, Nest, SmartThings Hub) is required for Apple Home/Alexa/Google Home/SmartThings platforms.
  • Offline-Ready Control：Once you've set up your Matter-certified devices on your LAN, they'll be able to communicate with each other directly, using the Matter protocol. This means that if your home internet connection goes offline, your Matter-certified devices will still be able to communicate and be controlled within your LAN, without relying on the internet or cloud services.
  • Remote Control from Anywhere：Use the app to turn electronics on before you arrive home and off after you leave, no matter where you are. Using the smart plug that work with alexa manage your power usage and save money.
  • Hands-free Voice Control：Control the plug using simple voice commands through Apple HomeKit, Siri, Amazon Alexa, Google Assistant, and SmartThings, without the need for physical input such as buttons or switches.
  • Flexible Scheduling & Timer：Effortlessly reduce energy usage with automatic device shutdown after a set time. For example Chrismas Tree, TV, Lamp, Fan, Humidifier,Blenders, Lightbulbs
  • Design with Safty and Compact：Beysen smart plugs are FCC certified with fire-resistant materials and provide 1250W 10A power capacity, as well as protection against short-circuits and overloads. Despite safety features, the smart outlet plug has a small form factor that won't take up too much space.
  • Important Tips：Beysen smart plug only support 2.4GHz WiFi and IPv6 network. A Matter-certified hub or controller (e.g., HomePod, Echo Dot, Nest, SmartThings Hub) is required for Apple Home, Alexa, Google Home, SmartThings platforms.

      4.0 out of 5 starsAmazon Vine Customer Review of Free Product
      Decent smart home plugs, reasonably easy to set up, stick out from socket quite a bit.
      Reviewed in the United States on December 9, 2024
      Review of: "Matter" Smart Plugs That Work with Alexa & Google Home, ASIN: B0DJZ1BRPX\ First impressions review: These new smart plugs are made to work with "Matter", a newer open standard for interoperability with lots of smart home... See more
      Review of: "Matter" Smart Plugs That Work with Alexa & Google Home, ASIN: B0DJZ1BRPX\

      First impressions review:
      These new smart plugs are made to work with "Matter", a newer open standard for interoperability with lots of smart home things from different manufacturers.

      Unlike many smart plugs that seem to be wide and take over your outlets, potentially blocking another one, these smart plugs are fairly small and instead rather tall, sticking out from the outlet quite a bit. But, this form-factor would probably be better with a power strip, and using both wall outlets.

      I simply plugged one of these in to power, opened my Alexa app, and it had already discovered that the device existed nearby. But, it still needed to be set up, which included going through a process and either typing in a code printed on the device, or scanning a QR code on the device. Either option required me to unplug the device to get access to that information, which seemed kind of clunky, because you can't have the device found without plugging it in, and you can't get the code from the device, unless you're able to get right up in it's business while plugged in. However, thankfully I didn't have to download any more proprietary apps, or add an Alexa skill to make it all work, nor rely on a manufacturer's system to be there for years to come in order for my smart home to continue.

      Once set up, the smart plug works like any other. I named it in the Alexa app, and can use my Alexa devices to voice control. All major recent Amazon Echo products support Matter, so this makes this device a bit future proof, I hope.

      It's nice that these smart plugs are 3-prong, but it's kind of silly that for new plugs they still only support 2.4Ghz WiFi.

      But, for $7/plug, this seems like an excellent value, and I hope they last a long time.
